<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 94 / UK Company News: EFG dips but seeks acquisitions
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
EFG, the Oxford-based garden centre and horticultural products group, saw
pre-tax profits decline to Pounds 615,000 in the six months to July 31,
against Pounds 804,000.
The fall, struck despite a turnround to interest receivable of Pounds 56,000
(payable Pounds 148,000), came on turnover of Pounds 6.49m (Pounds 10m).
Stripping out discontinued activities, turnover showed an increase, the
company said.
Mr Robin Garland, chief executive, said that the main operations had
remained profitable in difficult market conditions. 'Strong cash flow and
proceeds from our rationalisation programme have considerably improved the
cash position and further strengthened the balance sheet.'
Earnings per share, on capital increased by last year's rights issue,
dropped from 3.02p to 1.31p.
</TEXT>
