<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 94 / Investors pledge Pounds 12m for Crest
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN, Investments Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sixty-nine City institutions, including the London Stock Exchange, have
subscribed for shares worth Pounds 12m in CrestCo, the holding company which
will own the new electronic share settlement system under development by the
Bank of England.
The funds are intended to finance the development of the system which is
expected to become operational late in 1996. However, none of the
shareholders will have voting rights in CrestCo during the build phase.
These will be held by the Bank of England and will only pass to shareholders
just before the start of live operations.
The Bank of England had been under pressure from the Treasury to ensure that
the costs of developing Crest were not incurred by taxpayers and had
therefore been anxious to obtain financing from the investment community
early in the project's develop-ment.
No shareholder will have a stake larger than 3 per cent and the biggest
investors, so-called Tier 1 organisations, will have subscribed for shares
worth Pounds 375,000 or Pounds 390,000. The Bank said the wide ownership
base was to ensure that Crest's pricing policy, operating regime or
development plans gave no undue advantage to any one commercial interest or
to any one community.
Tier-2 investors will subscribe for shares worth either Pounds 200,000 or
Pounds 210,000, while those in Tier 3 will have committed Pounds 100,000 per
organisation. Tier-4 shareholders will have committed Pounds 30,000 each.
Participants are subscribing for redeemable fixed dividend shares with a
nominal value of Pounds 250. They will give investors a return of 4
percentage points above the 8 3/4 per cent Treasury stock yield as at
October 25. The first dividend will be payable no later than 18 months after
the start of live operations.
Shareholders will first have the opportunity to sell their stakes two years
after the start when there will be a 'rebalancing' to adjust shareholdings
in relation to usage of the system.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>CrestCo.
</CO>
