<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 94 / Accord on HK airport 'soon'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE LUCAS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
An agreement on funding Hong Kong's new airport seems within reach. Mr Guo
Fengmin, China's representative to the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group
overseeing the 1997 handover of the territory, said yesterday he hoped
consensus could be reached by early November, when he retires. Negotiators
came near clinching the package in June, but fell at the last hurdle. This
time, an agreed minute, detailing that the airport and connected railway
project be funded by HKDollars 60.3bn (Pounds 5.06bn) of equity and
HKDollars 23bn of debt, is expected to be signed before Mr Guo leaves Hong
Kong. Signing of the Financial Support Agreements (FSAs), contracts proving
to bankers the project is viable, is expected to follow.
