<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 94 / World Trade News: Minerals boost for W Australia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PERTH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The value of Western Australia's mineral and petroleum exports rose by 3.5
per cent to ADollars 12.9bn (USDollars 9.4bn) in 1993-94 and is set to
accelerate in the coming year, the state's resources development department
said. Mr David Kelly, the department's chief executive, said the state
accounted for 43 per cent of the value of Australia's resource exports of
ADollars 29.8bn, 44 per cent of Australian mineral production, 29 per cent
of petroleum production and 57 per cent of new mining investment. Mr Kelly
said exports to Asia continued to grow strongly. Resource exports to China
and Korea rose 26 per cent to ADollars 911m and ADollars 1.16bn
respectively. Exports to Taiwan grew 13 per cent to ADollars 369m. However,
exports to Japan fell 0.4 per cent to ADollars 3.6bn, reflecting Japanese
economic conditions and lower iron ore and gas prices.
