the company has not forecast official figures for the first six months to
September, analysts expect an improvement in operational profits thanks to
cost-cutting efforts and the return of business-class passengers. From this
interim, companies are required to disclose unrealised losses on foreign
exchange trading, and the company's losses could be up to Y45bn (Dollars
464m).
