FT  24 OCT 94 / Letters to the Editor: A natural order of luxury
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr JORGE EDUARDO NAVARRETTE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I was very much amused by Tony Walker's dispatch on the use of luxury
cars by Chinese Communist party cadres ('Chinese officials lose a touch of
luxury', October 17). It is not the first time that an attempt to impose
austerity on them has been made.
I was in Peking in late 1989, when the dust of the infamous Tiananmen Square
'incident' was starting to settle and when a similar directive was issued.
It produced a very funny result: high officials were driven in old
Chinese-made cars, followed by two or more shining deluxe European cars
stuffed with security personnel. After several weeks the natural order of
things was quietly restored. I assume the same will happen again.
Jorge Eduardo Navarrette,
Mexican Embassy,
