<HEADLINE>
FT  24 OCT 94 / Singapore quizzes US academic
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KIERAN COOKE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KUALA LUMPUR
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US and Singapore are at loggerheads over the case of a Singapore-based
American academic, only months after arguing over Singapore's caning of a US
teenager. Mr Christopher Lingle, professor of European studies at the
National University of Singapore, has been questioned by police over an
article in the International Herald Tribune referring to 'intolerant
