<HEADLINE>
FT  24 OCT 94 / Cambodian minister to quit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JONATHAN MILLER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CAMBODIA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Prince Norodom Sirivudh, Cambodian foreign minister, said yesterday he was
resigning after the dismissal last week of his friend and ally, finance
minister Sam Rainsy. Prince Sirivudh had threatened to step down if Mr
Rainsy was removed from office. Officially, Mr Rainsy departed in the
interests of unity between the fractious partners in Cambodia's coalition
government. In reality, he had made too many enemies in his battle against
corruption, and had become too popular, too independent and too powerful. Mr
Rainsy had endeared himself to the international financial community through
his skills in economic management.
</TEXT>
