<HEADLINE>
FT  24 OCT 94 / Seoul city officials charged
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SEOUL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
South Korean prosecutors yesterday questioned six city officials and charged
five others with negligence over the Seoul bridge disaster in which 32 died.
Mayor Woo Myoung-Kyu ordered inspections of all 17 bridges in the city to
avoid a repetition of Friday's tragedy in which a span of the Songsu bridge
plunged into the Han River taking with it cars, vans and a bus. Former Mayor
Lee Won-jong, sacked hours after the bridge collapse, told parliamentary
hearings on the safety of Seoul bridges last week there was no cause for
concern. The collapse was the latest in a series of construction disasters
in South Korea which engineers blamed on shoddy work, poor quality control
and inadequate maintenance.
</TEXT>
